<title>GERMANY: Germany's BDI says wants efforts for EMU criteria.</title>
<headline>Germany's BDI says wants efforts for EMU criteria.</headline>
<dateline>COLOGNE, Germany 1997-06-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>The BDI German Association of Industry said on Monday further efforts are needed by nations seeking to meet entry criteria for the planned single European currency.</p>
<p>The BDI said further savings measures must be enforced in order to secure the stability of the currency, saying the currency should not be introduced in January 1999 at any price.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525</p>
